# Changelog

All notable changes to Village Wallet will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [2.0.0] - 2025-10-16

### ðŸŽ‰ Major Release - Multi-Token Support

### Added
- **Multi-Token Support**: USDT, USDC, DAI on all networks
- **3 New Networks**: Base, Optimism, BNB Chain (total: 6 networks)
- **Token Selector UI**: Choose between native tokens and stablecoins
- **USD Price Display**: Shows approximate USD value for amounts
- **Fallback RPC System**: Automatic failover for network connections
- **Network Status Indicator**: Green/red dot showing connection status
- **Network Badges**: Visual ticker badges showing current network
- **ERC-20 Token Support**: Full implementation for token transfers
- **Token Balance Checking**: View balances for any supported token
- **Chain IDs**: Proper chain identification for all networks

### Changed
- **Dark Mode Theme**: Complete redesign with navy + purple palette
- **Improved Error Handling**: Better NFC and network error messages
- **Settings UI**: Cleaner layout with better organization
- **Balance Screen**: Now shows selected token balance
- **Payment Flow**: Supports both native and ERC-20 tokens

### Fixed
- **Arbitrum Connection**: Updated RPC endpoint for better reliability
- **NFC Initialization**: App no longer crashes if NFC unavailable
- **Network Switching**: Smoother transitions between networks
- **Gas Estimation**: Accurate gas calculations for token transfers
- **Scrolling Issues**: Balance screen now fully scrollable

### Removed
- Test banner (production ready)
- Redundant network code
- Debug console logs

---

## [1.0.0] - 2025-09-15

### ðŸš€ Initial Release

### Added
- **NFC Card Support**: Read and write to NFC cards
- **3 Networks**: Polygon, Arbitrum, Ethereum
- **PIN Encryption**: Secure AES-256 encryption
- **ENS Support**: Use .eth names for addresses
- **Balance Checking**: View card balances
- **Payment Processing**: Merchant payment workflow
- **Network Switching**: Change between Polygon/Arbitrum/Ethereum
- **Flexible Serial Numbers**: Accept any card serial format
- **Settings Screen**: Configure merchant address and network

### Security
- AES-256 encryption for private keys
- PIN-based authentication
- No server-side key storage
- Keys cleared from memory after use

